HEADWORD: gonorrhœa
<hw>gon`or*rh⟦oe⟧"a</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>gonorrhoea</ets>, Gr. <?/; <?/
that which begets, semen, the genitals + <?/ to flow: cf. F.
<ets>gonorrh⟦eacute⟧e</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A contagious
inflammatory disease of the genitourinary tract, affecting especially
the urethra and vagina, and characterized by a mucopurulent discharge,
pain in urination, and chordee; clap. It is caused by infection with the
bacterium <spn>Neiseria gonorrheae</spn>, and is commonly transmitted by
sexual intercourse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

